LAGOS – The Strike Force of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) has intercepted 49 vehicles and other contraband with Duty Paid Value (DPV) of N126.8 million. The interception, DAILY INDEPENDENT gathered was made in Zone ‘B’ of the Service. Abdullahi Kirawa, National Coordinator of the strike force revealed this in Kaduna at the weekend. Kirawa, a Deputy Comptroller of Customs (DC) said the items were impounded between August 3 and September 20, 2018 in Kaduna axis. According to him, other contraband seized include 13, 983 bags of rice, 3, 983 Jerry cans of vegetable oil, 456 bales of second hand clothing, 70 bags of sugar and 50 cartons of spaghetti among others. Kirawa said the seizures were made following tip-offs from patriotic Nigerians, adding that citizens’ engagement assisted in the reduction of smuggling activities to barest minimum in the zone. He assured that the Service would not relent in its efforts to end smuggling in the country for the good of the economy and national growth. “Strike force officers and men will not relent in their efforts of ensuring that die-hard smugglers are arrested and prosecuted to serve as deterrent to others,” the customs boss assured. He, however, explained that the strike force, which was set up by the Controller General of Customs Col. Hameed Ali(rtd) has the mandate to ensure effective suppression of smuggling to facilitate increase revenue to government. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 